-tD9TpO3bbt35kPxPUPHiI0Zv9npHgZnOCy7i_UB3USUiBrGWvsHPfllfR0I";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:844;s:6:"height";i:721;s:6:"source";s:49:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/288652657364614741/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}i:18;a:11:{s:7:"keyword";s:26:"chair conformation bonding";s:4:"slug";s:26:"chair-conformation-bonding";s:5:"title";s:68:"Steps In Sn1 Mechanism Chemistry Lessons Organic Chemistry Chemistry";s:3:"alt";s:9:"pinterest";s:3:"url";s:76:"https://i.pinimg.com/originals/cd/0b/ec/cd0becb87828c2268f94d39d8ab730d0.png";s:5:"thumb";s:123:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcROSKqAEQGb6yRJkTjZRuBhBi8h23_oB9a-Hq58fk-__oLG7degC5tk3ic3CNbJAkaC8D0";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"png";s:5:"width";i:457;s:6:"height";i:737;s:6:"source";s:49:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/614248836663295015/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}i:19;a:11:{s:7:"keyword";s:26:"chair conformation bonding";s:4:"slug";s:26:"chair-conformation-bonding";s:5:"title";s:89:"The Covalent Bond Mcat Review Organic Chemistry Organic Chemistry Study Chemistry Lessons";s:3:"alt";s:9:"pinterest";s:3:"url";s:76:"https://i.pinimg.com/originals/43/06/1c/43061c3f9b4d40a82e5c9c1ad4cdacda.gif";s:5:"thumb";s:123:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRbr6fpPFI-14kagbKUnOddrGLqe4ef1FXB91EgU5XE4v489BJA7OWjIXVEzSiy-HsKTtE";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"gif";s:5:"width";i:333;s:6:"height";i:463;s:6:"source";s:49:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/272467846182392907/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}i:20;a:11:{s:7:"keyword";s:26:"chair conformation bonding";s:4:"slug";s:26:"chair-conformation-bonding";s:5:"title";s:52:"Alkane Chemistry Education Methane Organic Chemistry";s:3:"alt";s:9:"pinterest";s:3:"url";s:76:"https://i.pinimg.com/originals/d6/d5/c3/d6d5c31265364f5b5826394e292d770c.png";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcSd7HGroWissZdIOxa7zonr3vVq9XfZVs7PHQ";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"png";s:5:"width";i:220;s:6:"height";i:220;s:6:"source";s:48:"https://ar.pinterest.com/pin/289145238555388660/";s:6:"domain";s:16:"ar.pinterest.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:51:{i:0;s:174:"The definition of chair conformation is the lowest energy conformation for cyclohexane in which all bond angles are fairly close to 1095 and all hydrogen atoms are staggered.";i:1;s:130:"The chair conformation is considered to be the lowest energy conformation because it lacks both angle strain and torsional strain.";i:2;s:75:"This means that the chair conformation is the structure that is observable.";i:3;s:113:"In a chair conformation Fig1 all of the carboncarbon bond angles are 1095 o and are thereby free of angle strain.";i:4;s:59:"The chair conformation is free of torsional strain as well.";i:5;s:176:"The chair conformation being the most stable and predominant form of cyclohexane is non-planar with the headrest and footrest bonds lying above and below the planar seat bonds.";i:6;s:161:"The stability is a consequence of no angle strain owing to the almost tetrahedral C-C-C bond angles and no torsional strain due to the perfectly staggered bonds.";i:7;s:81:"The chair conformation cannot deform without changing the bond angles or lengths.";i:8;s:131:"We can think of it as two chains mirror images one of the other containing atoms 1-2-3-4 and 1-6-5-4 with opposite dihedral angles.";i:9;s:87:"The distance from atom 1 to atom 4 depends on the absolute value of the dihedral angle.";i:10;s:222:"Once the first bond is drawn in a Newman projection of a chair conformation of cyclohexane ring all of the other bonds axial and equatorial are fixed by the staggered arrangements and the cyclic connections to one another.";i:11;s:114:"Once you have drawn all of the bonds in a Newman projection you merely fill in the blanks at the end of each line.";i:12;s:97:"The bond angle in chair conformation is 1095 similar to the bond angle in a tetrahedral geometry.";i:13;s:136:"In fact cyclohexane take the chair conformation to achieve a bond angle similar to the tetrahedral geometry to eliminate angular strain.";i:14;s:110:"Here are videos where I full explain the chair conformation and why it happens along with its stereoisomerism.";i:15;s:205:"The Chair Conformation The stability data in Table 71 require that the bond angles in cyclohexane must be essentially the same as the bond angles in an alkanevery close to the ideal 1095 tetrahedral angle.";i:16;s:117:"If the bond angles were signiﬁcantly distorted from tetrahedral we would expect to see a greater heat of formation.";i:17;s:284:"The easiest way to draw equatorial bonds on the chair conformation is to make them parallel to the cyclohexane ring line that is the second line moving clockwise or counter-clockwise around the ring from the carbon youre drawing the equatorial bond on see the highlighted lines below.";i:18;s:95:"Two or more monosaccharides are joined by condensation reactions it results in the loss of H20.";i:19;s:121:"They are joined by a glycosidic bond- which is when C1 loses a H and lets say C4 loses a OH to result in a loss of water.";i:20;s:30:"The C1 and C4 are joined by O.";i:21;s:39:"This is known as a 1-4 glycosidic bond.";i:22;s:44:"Chair Conformation and Ring Flips - YouTube.";i:23;s:80:"The chair structure of cyclohexane is considered to be the perfect conformation.";i:24;s:108:"The chair structure consists of a six-membered ring where every C-C bond exists in a staggered conformation.";i:25;s:102:"With no torsional strain and no angle strain cyclohexane is the most stable of all the small rings of.";i:26;s:101:"This specific conformation that we are going to look at in a moment is called the chair conformation.";i:27;s:306:"NB that your cyclohexane might not initially be in this conformation if you are very unlucky and have somehow managed to arrange the atoms in such a manner that they are closer to one of the other conformations than the chair one and in that case we will have to rearrange them to our desired conformation.";i:28;s:57:"Can a chair conformation include a double bond on a ring.";i:29;s:296:"Take a molecule i made up rn 1-hydroxy-3-methyl-5-cyclohexene this drawn is in the shape of a ring has a hydroxy at the top and a methane at the 3rd spot and a double bond on the fifth and 6th carbon could i draw this on a chair conformation i assume not because of the pi bond but i am not sure.";i:30;s:134:"This is due to the formation of a seven-membered intramolecular hydrogen-bonded ring structure that stabilizes the chair conformation.";i:31;s:132:"Thus the strong tendency of the phenoxy group to be in an axial position is diminished by the internal hydrogen bonding interaction.";i:32;s:79:"Computational studies provided strong support for the experimental observation.";i:33;s:307:"The two possible chair conformations I and II of methyl 234-tri-O-methyl-a-D- glucoside Ri OMe Rg H are shown below I IT In the conformation I the primary hydroxyl could bond either to the oxygen on 6-membered ring or to the ring oxygen 5-membered ring and the respective absorption frequencies would be ca.";i:34;s:22:"3550 cm1 and 3600 cm1.";i:35;s:111:"To begin start by drawing two lines that are parallel to each other but not perfectly horizontal as shown here.";i:36;s:76:"Next add a downward-pointing V tip to one end this is the tail of the chair.";i:37;s:84:"Finally add an upward-pointing V tip to the other end this is the nose of the chair.";i:38;s:68:"The steps involved in drawing the chair conformation of cyclohexane.";i:39;s:87:"Axial and equatorial are types of bonds found in the chair conformation of cyclohexane.";i:40;s:70:"The chair conformation is the most stable conformation of cyclohexane.";i:41;s:117:"Axial positions are perpendicular to the plane of the ring and equatorial positions are around the plane of the ring.";i:42;s:46:"The bond angles in this conformation are 1109.";i:43;s:81:"The most stable conformation of cyclohexane is the chair form shown to the right.";i:44;s:78:"The C-C-C bonds are very close to 1095 o so it is almost free of angle strain.";i:45;s:77:"It is also a fully staggered conformation and so is free of torsional strain.";i:46;s:85:"Rotate the molecule in the JSMOL image to show this just like a Newman projection so.";i:47;s:89:"Axial position is the vertical chemical bonding in the chair conformation of cyclohexane.";i:48;s:119:"Due to the minimized steric hindrance the chair conformation is the most stable structure for the cyclohexane molecule.";i:49;s:76:"The axial position is perpendicular to the plane of the ring of cyclohexane.";i:50;s:55:"Therefore we can define it as a vertical chemical bond.";}}